The paper presents a hash algorithm for data storage applications, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the algorithm is designed to evenly divide the key space among the buckets and workload when the number of buckets changes, which relates to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. The paper also discusses the limitations of the algorithm, which could be relevant to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The algorithm's speed and memory efficiency could also be of interest to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on consistent hashing could make it relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
